label: [sound] Jingle Bells
info: ### Jingle Bells [Jingle Bells](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jingle_Bells) composed by James Lord Pierpont, 1857. This is a somewhat tongue-in-cheek use of Node-RED and not to be taken all that seriously. Can be played the [serverless Node-RED](http://cdn.flowhub.org/?t=0&fhid=5299e45175c85820) instanace. Even though this might seem frivoulous, it does demonstrate some nice features of Node-RED: 1. Reuse of code using link-call node The link-call node, in combination with the link-in and link-out nodes makes for simply code reuse. Those code is written once and reused often. 2. Abstraction of concepts The notes are defined as a serious of frequencies but then referred to as notes. 3. Encapsulation is visible Groups cluster functionality together: notes are clustered, individuals song-lines are clustered and then the final song is clustered together. This is visual and becomes understandable. ### Resources - https://mypianonotes.com/jingle-bells - https://muted.io/note-frequencies/ - https://pages.mtu.edu/~suits/notefreqs.html
